White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre addressed the ongoing conflict in Israel, expressing condolences for the lives lost and the devastating impact on families. She mentioned that 22 Americans have lost their lives and 17 remain unaccounted for. The President will be meeting with Jewish community leaders to discuss the administration's support for Israel and its strategy to counter antisemitism. Admiral John Kirby from the National Security Council provided updates on the situation, stating that efforts are being made to recover American hostages held by Hamas. He emphasized the United States' support for Israel and its commitment to providing military assistance and defense-related support. The US is also actively working on establishing a safe passage corridor for civilians in Gaza. Kirby mentioned that Hezbollah and Iran are among the actors in the region that the US is concerned about. He also addressed the situation in Ukraine and announced a new aid package to support the country's defense efforts.